<subSubSection id="459D7EBDFFC3FFDFFF3CFF3D49326601" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC3FFDFFF3CFF3D49326601" blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDFFF3CFF3D4C5367B3" bold="true" box="[151,279,151,177]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A species of the 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC3FFDFFE4CFF324FB567B3" authorityName="Prokofiev and Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" box="[487,753,152,177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aphos">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDFFE4CFF324FB567B3" box="[487,753,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Pseudoscopelus aphos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, which can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC3FFDFFA9DFF3248D867B3" authorityName="Prokofiev and Kukuev, 2006 Pseudoscopelus parini Prokofiev and Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" box="[1334,1436,152,177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parini">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDFFA9DFF3248D867B3" box="[1334,1436,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. parini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the complete absence photophores or clear lines on body (
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDFFCC3FF6B4ECC67D8" box="[872,904,193,218]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">vs.</emphasis>
clear lines in place of photophores in ventral part of body in 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC3FFDFFEE7FF434F126600" authorityName="Prokofiev and Kukuev, 2006 Pseudoscopelus parini Prokofiev and Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" box="[332,598,233,258]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parini">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDFFEE7FF434F126600" box="[332,598,233,258]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Pseudoscopelus parini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and photophores present in all other species).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="459D7EBDFFC3FFDFFF6DFEBB4E0C6110" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="description">
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC3FFDFFF6DFEBB4F74667E" blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDFFF6DFEBB4C1A6629" bold="true" box="[198,350,273,299]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Description.</emphasis>
Medium-sized species of 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC3FFDFFD36FEBB4E1C6628" box="[669,856,273,298]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDFFD36FEBB4E1C6628" box="[669,856,273,298]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Pseudoscopelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, largest specimen examined 
<quantity id="CA7F80D3FFC3FFDFFB1CFEBB48666629" box="[1207,1314,273,299]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.07" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="60.7">60.7 mm</quantity>
SL. Morphometric data summarized in 
<tableCitation id="4005188DFFC3FFDFFDAFFE904F1A6656" box="[516,606,314,340]" captionStart="TABLE 8" captionStartId="52.[151,241,157,181]" captionText="TABLE 8. Morphometric data for Pseudoscopelus aphos (n=5) and P.parini (n=7). SD stands for standard deviation." pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Table 8</tableCitation>
. General body shape as described for genus with diagnostic characteristics of species and species group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC3FFDFFF6DFE204C5A651C" blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">First dorsal-fin rays vii (1), viii (2), ix (2); second dorsal-fin rays xxiii (1), xxiv (1), xxvii (1), ii+21 (2); anal-fin rays iii+20 (2), iii+21 (2), iii+23 (1); pectoral-fin rays 12 (1), 14 (1), 15 (1); pelvic-fin rays I+5 (5); caudal-fin rays i+7+8+i (4), i+8+7+i (1). Branchiostegal rays 7 (5). Pre-caudal vertebrae 18 (2); total vertebrae 36 (2).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC3FFDFFF6DFD864C5865C2" blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Lateral line complete; lateral-line pores 74 (1), 75 (1), 76 (1), 77 (2). Pores in temporal canal 2 (5); supratemporal canal 3 (5); otic canal 2 (5); supraorbital canal 5 (5); supranasal pore 4 (5); epiphyseal branch 3 (5); infraorbital canal 12 (5); preopercular canal 5 (3), 6 (2); mandibular canal 6 (5); fifth pore of mandibular canal 1 (3).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC3FFDFFF6DFD644DAC643B" blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDFFF6DFD644C0765EA" bold="true" box="[198,323,718,744]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Dentition.</emphasis>
Enlarged teeth on premaxilla, dentary and palatine. Teeth arrangement as illustrated for 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC3FFDFFAF2FD654C396412" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scriptus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDFFAF2FD654C396412" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Pseudoscopelus scriptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Premaxilla moderately wide, widest point of premaxillary body 10–14 % in premaxillary length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC3FFDFFF6DFCE24E0C632E" blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Premaxillary teeth on head, neck, body and caudal process. Lateral series in single longitudinal row, along lateral edge of premaxillary head, neck, body and caudal process; teeth conical, slightly curved. Canine and fang on ventral shelf of premaxillary head. Middle and mesial series of premaxilla on ventral shelf of body. Middle series in two, irregular, longitudinal rows; teeth needle-like, straight, gradually increasing in size from lateral to medial. Mesial series in transverse rows, each row with three to four teeth; teeth needle-like, slightly curved, gradually increasing in size from medial to mesial.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC3FFDFFF6DFB914CD463CC" blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Dentary teeth in lateral and mesial series. Lateral series along lateral shelf of dentary, in single, longitudinal row, extending from symphysis to posterior tip; teeth conical, slightly curved. Mesial series in transverse rows of one to four teeth; teeth straight, needle-like, gradually increasing in size from lateral to mesial. Palatine teeth 3 (4), 5 (1).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC3FFDFFF6DFB77494A6272" blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
Teeth on infrapharyngobranchials and fifth ceratobranchial, conical, curved. Teeth on second basibranchial 9 (1), 10 (2), 11 (1), 12 (1), conical, in 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDFFD06FAAF4FF8621C" box="[685,700,1285,1310]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">V</emphasis>
-shaped or two rows. Teeth absent on basihyal and other basibranchials. Gill rakers on first epibranchial 0 (5); first ceratobranchial 8 (2), 9 (1), 11 (1), 14 (1); first hypobranchial 4 (1), 5 (1), 6 (2), 9 (1). Gill rakers absent on other elements.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC3FFDFFF6DFAD4491762E8" blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDFFF6DFAD44C56629A" bold="true" box="[198,274,1406,1432]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Color.</emphasis>
Specimens preserved for long time faded to light brown. Body uniformly dark brown, including skin on epiphyseal branch. Pectoral, pelvic, first and second dorsal, and anal fins slightly pigmented at their bases; caudal fin black or dark brown. Internal area of mouth and gill arches pale.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC3FFDFFF6DFA524E0C6110" blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" box="[198,840,1528,1554]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDFFF6DFA524C8E6110" bold="true" box="[198,458,1528,1554]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Luminescent organs.</emphasis>
Photophores completely absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="459D7EBDFFC3FFDFFF6DF98A49E56161" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC3FFDFFF6DF98A485C6139" blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" box="[198,1304,1568,1595]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDFFF6DF98A4C236138" bold="true" box="[198,359,1568,1594]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Distribution.</emphasis>
In the western North Atlantic; from 
<geoCoordinate id="68B34BF1FFC3FFDFFCBEF98B4E1C6139" box="[789,856,1569,1595]" degrees="24" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" precision="55555" value="24.0">24º N</geoCoordinate>
to 
<geoCoordinate id="68B34BF1FFC3FFDFFCD6F98B4E876139" box="[893,963,1569,1595]" degrees="40" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" precision="55555" value="40.0">40º N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="68B34BF1FFC3FFDFFC64F98B495C6139" box="[975,1048,1569,1595]" degrees="50" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" precision="55555" value="-50.0">50º W</geoCoordinate>
to 
<geoCoordinate id="68B34BF1FFC3FFDFFB95F98B49C36139" box="[1086,1159,1569,1595]" degrees="76" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" precision="55555" value="-76.0">76º W</geoCoordinate>
(
<figureCitation id="95BC31B3FFC3FFDFFB3CF98B484F6139" box="[1175,1291,1569,1595]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="53.[151,255,735,759]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,391,713]" captionTargetId="figure-639@53.[153,1438,381,717]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="FIGURE 23. Map of distribution of (A) Pseudoscopelus aphos (diamond), P. lavenbergi (cross), and P. parini (circle); (B) P. astronesthidens (cross), P. australis (asterisk), and P. odontoglossum (star). Each symbol may represent more than one locality; solid symbols represent type localities." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6031466" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6031466/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 23 A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC3FFDFFF6DF9E249E56161" blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" box="[198,1185,1608,1635]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDFFF6DF9E24F416160" bold="true" box="[198,517,1608,1634]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Bathymetric distribution.</emphasis>
Meso- to bathypelagic, from 
<quantity id="CA7F80D3FFC3FFDFFCCAF9E349486161" box="[865,1036,1609,1635]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.27" metricValueMax="16.34" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="m" value="927.0" valueMax="1634.0" valueMin="220.0">220 to 1634 m</quantity>
(mean 667).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="459D7EBDFFC3FFDCFF6DF9DB4F9267D8" lastPageId="50" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC3FFDFFF6DF9DB4810602F" blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDFFF6DF9DB4C7B6189" bold="true" box="[198,319,1649,1675]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="691650C7FFC3FFDFFEE0F9D84FF2618E" author="Prokofiev and Kukuev" box="[331,694,1650,1676]" firstAuthor="Prokofiev" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="712 - 729" refId="ref59420" refString="Prokofiev, A. M. &amp; Kukuev, E. I. (2005) Preliminary review of the Atlantic linebellies of the genus Pseudoscopelus with remarks on the species composition of the genus in the world's fauna (Perciformes, Chiasmodontidae). I. Voprosy Ikhtyologii, 45, 749 - 767 (in Russian, English translation Journal of Ichthyology, 45, 712 - 729)." type="journal article" year="2005">Prokofiev and Kukuev (2005)</bibRefCitation>
presented an erroneous description of color. They based the description on a poorly preserved specimen, which was collected in 1977 and kept in formalin since then; the bones were uncalcified and the overall color was faded to brown, typical of museum specimens. They described the color of internal area of mouth as black; in fact there are some melanophores on the skin of premaxilla and dentary, especially on dentigerous areas and on basibranchials, which gives a dusky aspect.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC3FFDCFF6DF8964F9267D8" blockId="49.[151,1440,151,1999]" lastBlockId="50.[151,1435,152,218]" lastPageId="50" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
The data presented herein is based on a reasonable amount of specimens from the 
<typeStatus id="D23C9394FFC3FFDFFB3EF89649836054" box="[1173,1223,1852,1878]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">type</typeStatus>
locality and adjacent areas. Some specimens are in great shape and have well-preserved pigmentation allowing this to be a more accurate description. The internal areas of mouth and gill arches are demonstrated in 
<figureCitation id="95BC31B3FFC3FFDFFB7AF827482660A5" box="[1233,1378,1933,1959]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="41.[151,255,1820,1844]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,860,1796]" captionTargetId="figure-288@41.[151,1436,859,1797]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 19. Pseudoscopelus paxtoni: (A) NMNZ P. 28657, 205.1 mm, holotype; (B) MNMZ P. 37858, 200.4 mm, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6031454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6031454/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Figure 19 B</figureCitation>
; it is not as back as described. Based on such mistake, 
<bibRefCitation id="691650C7FFC3FFDFFD41F81F490A60CD" author="Prokofiev and Kukuev" box="[746,1102,1973,1999]" firstAuthor="Prokofiev" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" refId="ref59719" refString="Prokofiev, A. M. &amp; Kukuev, E. I. (2008) Systematics and Distribution of the swallowerfishes of the genus Pseudoscopelus (Chiasmodontidae). KMK Scientific Press Ltd., Moscow, 162 p." type="book" year="2008">Prokofiev and Kukuev (2008)</bibRefCitation>
diagnosed 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC3FFDFFB7CF81C487F60CD" authorityName="Prokofiev and Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" box="[1239,1339,1974,1999]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aphos">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDFFB7CF81C487F60CD" box="[1239,1339,1974,1999]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. aphos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC3FFDCFA2DF81C4D9B67B3" authorityName="Prokofiev and Kukuev, 2006 Pseudoscopelus parini Prokofiev and Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="50" lastPageNumber="51" order="Perciformes" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parini">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC3FFDCFA2DF81C4D9B67B3" italics="true" lastPageId="50" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. parini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[see species comments for discussion on species’ status and synonyms], and suggested that it might be related to the 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC0FFDCFE9CFF6B4C8667D8" authorityName=", YPM" authorityYear="2798" box="[311,450,193,218]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="altipinnis">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC0FFDCFE9CFF6B4C8667D8" box="[311,450,193,218]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">P. altipinnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC0FFDCFE57FF6B4F8B67D8" authorityName="Prokofiev and Kukuev, 2006 Pseudoscopelus astronesthidens Prokofiev and Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" box="[508,719,193,218]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="astronesthidens">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC0FFDCFE57FF6B4F8B67D8" box="[508,719,193,218]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">P. astronesthidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
